OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,419,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41802
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F418A1779393955
OL,3,CRoses bloom 'weeks early' as climate
OL,4,Cchange upends flowering patterns
OL,6,FBut when the rose garden at Mottisfont
OL,7,Fwas officially donated to the National
OL,8,FTrust on June 30 1972, it was in peak
OL,9,Fflower, the charity said ` with head
OL,10,Fgardeners seeing regular changes to
OL,11,Fflowering patterns since.
OL,13,FThe peak blooming of the roses has
OL,14,Fshifted by the equivalent of one day
OL,15,Fevery two-and-a-half years, as a
OL,16,Fresult of rising temperatures and
OL,17,Fchanging weather patterns, the
OL,18,FNational Trust said.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G2/9
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,419,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41803
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F418A1779393955
OL,3,CRoses bloom 'weeks early' as climate
OL,4,Cchange upends flowering patterns
OL,6,FIt is a similar story at other
OL,7,FNational Trust gardens in the south of
OL,8,FEngland, such as Anglesey Abbey,
OL,9,FCambridgeshire, Buckland Abbey, Devon
OL,10,Fand Chartwell in Kent ` but more
OL,11,Fnorthern properties are seeing more
OL,12,Ftypical flowering, according to the
OL,13,Fcharity.
OL,15,FMottisfont head gardener Rob Ballard
OL,16,Fsaid: "After a very wet, warm winter,
OL,17,Fincluding 42 consecutive days of rain
OL,18,Fat the start of the year, the roses
OL,19,Fgot off to an early start.
OL,26,@xD@GOU
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/9
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,419,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41804
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F418A1779393955
OL,3,CRoses bloom 'weeks early' as climate
OL,4,Cchange upends flowering patterns
OL,6,F"Then warm spells in April accelerated
OL,7,Fgrowth, and this year they're
OL,8,Fflowering earlier than we can
OL,9,Fremember."
OL,11,FThe changing climate also means the
OL,12,Fteam is having to adapt the way the
OL,13,Frose garden, and the wider site, is
OL,14,Fmanaged, from caring for the soil to
OL,15,Fpruning roses differently, he said.
OL,17,FMr Ballard added: "We've mulched the
OL,18,Fwhole garden to lock in water,
OL,19,Fsuppress weeds and build organic
OL,20,Fmatter in the soil.
OL,26,@nD@AOUqD@JO]yD@SOU
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/9
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,419,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41805
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F418A1779393955
OL,3,CRoses bloom 'weeks early' as climate
OL,4,Cchange upends flowering patterns
OL,6,F"It supports everything from the roses
OL,7,Fthemselves to the worm population
OL,8,Fbeneath them."
OL,10,FHe said: "We're adjusting our pruning
OL,11,Fto let roses such as Adelaide
OL,12,Fd'Orleans grow in a more natural way
OL,13,Fand thinking longer-term about the
OL,14,Fright plant in the right place, better
OL,15,Fwater management, and conserving rare
OL,16,Fvarieties so they survive for
OL,17,Fgenerations to come."
OL,26,@nD@AOUpD@NO]rD@JOUyD@UO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G5/9
