OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,419,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41808
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F418A1779393955
OL,3,CRoses bloom 'weeks early' as climate
OL,4,Cchange upends flowering patterns
OL,6,FNational Trust horticultural
OL,7,Fspecialist Rebecca Bevan said earlier
OL,8,Fflowering was not necessarily harmful,
OL,9,Fbut climate change still posed threats
OL,10,Fto roses.
OL,12,FShe said: "The bigger concern is water
OL,13,Favailability.
OL,15,F"Research shows that drought poses the
OL,16,Fgreatest threat to roses, so we're
OL,17,Ffocusing on building healthy soils,
OL,18,Fchoosing tougher varieties and
OL,19,Finvesting in water capture and
OL,20,Fstorage."
OL,26,@tD@KOUwD@AOU|D@IO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G8/9
